9 Relating to expungement; to amend Sections 15-27-1,
10 15-27-2, 15-27-4, and 15-27-5, Code of Alabama 1975, as last
11 amended by Act 2025-427, 2025 Regular Session, to further
12 provide for the right to expungement; to authorize the
13 expungement of overturned or vacated convictions; to authorize
14 the expungement of pardoned offenses; and to provide minimum
15 hearing requirements for an expungement petition.
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
17 Section 1. Sections 15-27-1, 15-27-2, 15-27-4, and
18 15-27-5, Code of Alabama 1975, as last amended by Act
19 2025-427, 2025 Regular Session, are amended to read as
20 follows:
21 "§15-27-1
22 (a) A person who has been charged with a misdemeanor
23 offense, violation, traffic violation, boating violation, or
24 municipal ordinance violation may file a petition in the
25 criminal division of the circuit court in the county in which
26 the charges were filed, to expunge records relating to the
27 charge in any of the following circumstances:
28 (1) When the charge has been dismissed with prejudice
