365 The court shall have discretion over the number of cases that
366 may be expunged pursuant to this chapter after the first case
367 is expunged.
368 (f) The ruling of the court shall be subject to appeal
369 and may not be reversed absent a showing of an abuse of
370 discretionunless the ruling is clearly erroneous."
